abstract: About 37 million Americans tuned in on Tuesday, the smallest audience of President Trump’s tenure.

lead_paragraph: President Trump put a “Celebrity Apprentice” spin on his State of the Union address on Tuesday, seeding the 78-minute broadcast with surprise reveals and viral moments: a tear-stained reunion of a military family, a snubbed handshake and an impromptu bestowing of the Presidential Medal of Freedom to a guest star, the radio host Rush Limbaugh.

abstract: The growing extremism of the debate alienates many people on the left and right.
snippet: The growing extremism of the debate alienates many people on the left and right.
lead_paragraph: Where will abortion opponents stand in 2020? President Trump recently made his bid for their votes, becoming the first president to speak in person at the annual March for Life in Washington, an event held since 1974. Two days later, a Democratic presidential hopeful, Pete Buttigieg, told a woman who called herself a “proud pro-life Democrat” that he would not support more moderate abortion language in the Democratic National Committee platform — basically suggesting that, on this issue, she will not find affirmation or support from her party.

abstract: The senator from Utah was the first — and only — Republican to announce he supported removing the president from office.
snippet: The senator from Utah was the first — and only — Republican to announce he supported removing the president from office.
lead_paragraph: Senator Mitt Romney, Republican of Utah, announced on the Senate floor on Wednesday that he intended to vote to convict President Trump of abuse of power. He was the only Republican to break with his party and support removing Mr. Trump from office.

abstract: The proposed order, called “Making Federal Buildings Beautiful Again,” favors classical design for buildings in Washington. It has drawn opposition from architects.
snippet: The proposed order, called “Making Federal Buildings Beautiful Again,” favors classical design for buildings in Washington. It has drawn opposition from architects.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Should every new government building in the nation’s capital be created in the same style as the White House?

snippet: Mr. Madoff, who ran the largest Ponzi scheme in history, told a court that he had less than 18 months to live.
lead_paragraph: Bernard L. Madoff, the mastermind of the largest Ponzi scheme in history, said in a court filing on Wednesday that he was dying and asked for an early release from prison.
